==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Preciosity
<hw>Pre`ci*os"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>-ties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧ciosit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, OF. also
<ets>precieuset⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>Fastidious refinement, esp.
in language; specif., the affected purism and sententiousness
characteristic of the French pr⟦eacute⟧cieuses of the 17th
century.</def></p>

<p><q>He had the fastidiousness, the <qex>preciosity</qex>, the love of
archaisms, of your true decadent.</q> <rj><qau>L.
Douglas.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precious</ent>⟦br⟧
